Cape Town authorities have decided not to relocate homeless people in the city until further notice. This after several homeless people tested positive for TB. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Cape Town authorities have decided not to relocate homeless people in the city until further notice. This after several homeless people tested positive for TB. READ: Soshanguve High School burnt down The City of Cape Town was planning to continue rounding up homeless people and take them to the designated facility at the Strandfontein sports field. The plan has now been placed on hold. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.